WEBVTT

1
00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:06.000
Oh boy!
This global warming is killing me!

2
00:03:05.900 --> 00:03:09.800
This
is too hot..the ice age was too cold..

3
00:03:10.100 --> 00:03:12.700
What would it take to make you happy?

4
00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:16.000
This.. I like!

5
00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:00.500
No running Jane! Camp rules..

6
00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:04.300
Make me. Sloth!

7
00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:06.100
Make me...sir!

8
00:04:06.900 --> 00:04:08.200
It’s all about respect...

9
00:04:11.200 --> 00:04:13.100
Sarah. You just ate! Wait an hour!

10
00:04:13.100 --> 00:04:15.600
Hector! No.no! You can't pee-pee there!

11
00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:17.300
Ok.ok! there is fine..

12
00:04:17.400 --> 00:04:19.200
Ashley! Stop picking your...

13
00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:20.600
Pinata!

14
00:04:20.800 --> 00:04:21.800
Stop!

15
00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:24.000
...you're supposed to wear blindfolds!

16
00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:25.300
Ok!

17
00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:27.800
Hey. it's my turn to hit the sloth!

18
00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:31.300
..mine..mine...mine....mine!

19
00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.100
Hey! You didn't have any candy in you!

20
00:04:38.400 --> 00:04:40.100
Let’s bury him!!

21
00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:48.500
Hey. hey! Whoah..
Who said you kids can torture the sloth?

22
00:04:48.400 --> 00:04:50.700
Manny. don't squash their creativity..

23
00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:52.700
Hey Manny! Diego!!

24
00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:54.600
My bad mammal jammel!

25
00:04:54.800 --> 00:04:56.500
Wanna give a sloth a hand?

26
00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:00.100
Look.. I opened my camp!

27
00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:01.500
Come forth and sit...

28
00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:02.900
It means camp of Sid!

29
00:05:02.900 --> 00:05:06.000
Congratulations.
You’re now an idiot in two languages..

30
00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:06.900
Shhhh...!

31
00:05:06.900 --> 00:05:08.900
…not in front of the K-l-D-G!

32
00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.500
These little guys love me! Right. Billy?

33
00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:13.000
Don’t make me eat you!

34
00:05:13.700 --> 00:05:16.400
Funny. kid!
That's why they're called kids!

35
00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:17.900
I told you Sid..

36
00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:20.300
You’re not qualified to run a camp..

37
00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:23.500
Oh! Since when do qualifications
have anything to do with childcare...?

38
00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:25.200
Besides. these kids look up to me..

39
00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:28.100
I’m a role model to them!

40
00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:30.600
I can see that..

41
00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:33.200
You guys never think I can do anything..

42
00:05:33.100 --> 00:05:35.600
but I’m an equal member of this herd!

43
00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:37.500
I made this herd...!

44
00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:41.000
...and you need
to start treating me with some respect!!

45
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:44.500
Come on! Sid!

46
00:05:44.400 --> 00:05:45.700
Sid! We were just kidding!!

47
00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:47.200
Hey!

48
00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:49.600
Let's play pin the tail on the mammoth!!

49
00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:52.300
Sid!

50
00:05:53.400 --> 00:05:55.500
Can you stop!

51
00:05:56.500 --> 00:05:59.400
I'm gonna get some respect!!

52
00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:03.000
I’ll show 'em!

53
00:06:04.200 --> 00:06:07.000
And so. in the end..

54
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:09.300
the little burro reached his mommy..

55
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:12.500
and they lived happily ever after..

56
00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:16.300
Good job!

57
00:06:16.300 --> 00:06:19.200
Question! Why does the burro go home?

58
00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:20.800
Why doesn't he stay with the rabbit?

59
00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:24.800
Because. He wanted to be with his family

60
00:06:24.700 --> 00:06:26.600
I think he should go with the girl burro!

61
00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:28.200
...That's a better love story!

62
00:06:28.600 --> 00:06:31.700
OK! Well. when you tell
your burro story. that’s what he'll do.

63
00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:33.200
'Burro' is a demeaning name...

64
00:06:33.300 --> 00:06:35.400
Technically. it's called a wild ass!

65
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.500
Fine. The wild ass boy came home...

66
00:06:38.500 --> 00:06:40.100
...to his wild ass mother...

67
00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:44.300
See! That’s why I called it a burro!

68
00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:47.300
Could the burro have a grazing problem?

69
00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:49.900
- That would make him more...relatable..
-Boring!

70
00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:51.500
It’s not believable!

71
00:06:51.500 --> 00:06:54.000
- Do burrows eat their young?
- It's not a very satisfying ending!

72
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.300
Sometimes I throw up!

73
00:06:57.100 --> 00:06:58.700
They lived happily ever after...

74
00:06:58.700 --> 00:07:01.500
You can't get more satisfying than that!

75
00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:03.200
One big happy family!

76
00:07:03.400 --> 00:07:04.800
That’s the way it’s supposed to be!

77
00:07:04.700 --> 00:07:07.200
Then. where's your big. happy family?

78
00:07:12.300 --> 00:07:15.400
Then...the
hungry tiger eat the pesky little kids!!

79
00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:20.300
- You ok. buddy?
- Sure. why not?!

80
00:07:20.300 --> 00:07:23.600
- I just thought you..
- Storytimes over....the end!

81
00:07:23.500 --> 00:07:25.200
- Out of the way! Run for your lives!
- Hey. watch it!

82
00:07:25.100 --> 00:07:26.400
Where's everybody going?

83
00:07:26.400 --> 00:07:27.900
The world's coming to an end!

84
00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:29.500
What are you talking about?

85
00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:32.400
Fast Tony!
He says the world's going to flood!

86
00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:35.500
Folks.
I hold in my hand a device so powerful..

87
00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:36.600
it can actually pull air...

88
00:07:36.600 --> 00:07:38.300
right out of the sky!!

89
00:07:38.400 --> 00:07:40.400
Gather round...gather round!

90
00:07:41.200 --> 00:07:43.700
Pardon me. do you have gills ma'am?

91
00:07:43.600 --> 00:07:45.600
So you can't breathe under water?

92
00:07:46.200 --> 00:07:48.100
My assistant here will demonstrate!

93
00:07:48.400 --> 00:07:51.200
Hey. I can smell the ocean!

94
00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:52.300
What are you doing...?

95
00:07:52.200 --> 00:07:54.500
I can't sell that now...!!

96
00:07:54.400 --> 00:07:56.700
You suck
air through your mouth you moron!!

97
00:07:57.400 --> 00:08:00.300
If you're a pupil
of mine. and I'm starting instruction...

98
00:08:00.200 --> 00:08:02.700
you'll
have plenty of air for eons to come!

99
00:08:03.200 --> 00:08:05.700
Of course. don't stay buried!

100
00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:08.700
Why are you scaring
everybody with this doomsday stuff?

101
00:08:09.700 --> 00:08:11.300
I’m trying to make a living here pal..

102
00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:15.600
It’s all part of my weather forecast!

103
00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:18.500
The 5 day outlook is calling
for intense flooding. followed by..

104
00:08:18.500 --> 00:08:20.600
the end of the world..!!

105
00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:22.900
With a slight chance of patchy sunshine

106
00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:24.100
..later in the week

107
00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:26.500
Come on! Don't listen to him..

108
00:08:26.300 --> 00:08:28.800
Fast Tony
would sell his own mother for a grape!

109
00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:30.200
Are you making an offer?

110
00:08:30.600 --> 00:08:33.100
I mean no! I would not!

111
00:08:33.300 --> 00:08:35.600
Haven’t you heard? The ice is melting!

112
00:08:35.600 --> 00:08:37.800
You see this ground? It's covered in ice

113
00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:40.200
A thousand
years ago it was covered in ice..

114
00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:41.400
A thousand years from now..

115
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.000
it will still be ice!

116
00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:48.100
Say. buddy..not to cast aspersions
on your survival instincts. but..

117
00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:50.600
haven't
mammoths pretty much gone extinct?

118
00:08:50.500 --> 00:08:51.600
What are you talking about?

119
00:08:51.600 --> 00:08:54.200
I’m talking
about you being the last of your kind!

120
00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:57.500
Ahh! Your breath smells like ants!

121
00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:01.700
Be as that as it may..

122
00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:04.100
When's
the last time you saw another mammoth?

123
00:09:05.200 --> 00:09:07.700
Ah! Don't pay any attention to him Manny

124
00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:09.300
Mammoths can't go extinct..

125
00:09:09.200 --> 00:09:10.800
they are the biggest things on earth!

126
00:09:10.800 --> 00:09:12.400
What about the dinosaurs?

127
00:09:12.400 --> 00:09:14.100
The dinosaurs got cocky!

128
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.600
They made enemies!
-Look!...

129
00:09:15.500 --> 00:09:18.000
some idiot's going down the eviscerator!

130
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.300
Please tell me that’s not our cue!

131
00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:26.200
OK..I'm goona jump on the count of 3!

132
00:09:27.600 --> 00:09:30.100
One.....

133
00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:31.100
Two.....

134
00:09:31.200 --> 00:09:34.700
Sid!
Don't move a muscle! We’re coming up!

135
00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:36.800
jump!..jump!...jump!..jump!..

136
00:09:36.700 --> 00:09:38.100
...jump. jump. jump. jump!

137
00:09:38.400 --> 00:09:39.300
Sorry..

138
00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.100
Two and three one thousands...

139
00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.800
Two and four one thousands...

140
00:09:43.800 --> 00:09:46.300
Sid!
What are you doing? Get down from there!

141
00:09:46.200 --> 00:09:48.900
No way! I’m going to be
the first to jump off the eviscerator...

142
00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:50.800
And then
you guys are gonna have to start..

143
00:09:50.700 --> 00:09:52.400
showing me some respect!

144
00:09:52.400 --> 00:09:54.500
You jump off this
and the only respect you're gonna get..

145
00:09:54.400 --> 00:09:55.700
is respect for the dead!

146
00:09:55.700 --> 00:09:58.200
Come on Manny! He's not that stupid..!

147
00:09:59.200 --> 00:10:01.000
But. I've been wrong before!

148
00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:02.500
Geronimo!!!

149
00:10:06.100 --> 00:10:07.200
Hey. watch it!

150
00:10:13.700 --> 00:10:15.300
I can't breath...

151
00:10:16.100 --> 00:10:18.300
I think I just coughed up my spleen!

152
00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:35.300
Ahh! Diego! Retract the claws please!

153
00:10:35.100 --> 00:10:36.900
Oh...right...sorry!

154
00:10:36.900 --> 00:10:39.000
You know.
if I didn't know you better Diego..

155
00:10:38.900 --> 00:10:40.900
I'd think you're afraid of the water..

156
00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:43.900
Ok..Ok! Good thing I know you better!

157
00:10:43.800 --> 00:10:45.100
Guys...!

158
00:10:45.600 --> 00:10:47.500
Fast Tony was right..!

159
00:10:48.700 --> 00:10:50.200
everything is melting!

160
00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:16.300
It’s all gonna flood...

161
00:11:16.600 --> 00:11:17.800
Come on! We’ve gotta warn them.

162
00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.800
Maybe we can
rapidly evolve into water creatures.

163
00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:23.400
That’s genius. Ed...

164
00:11:23.400 --> 00:11:24.900
Call me 'Squid'.

165
00:11:27.100 --> 00:11:29.300
Gees..this whole thing's a piece of junk!

166
00:11:29.400 --> 00:11:31.000
I can't believe I live here!

167
00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:35.600
What?

168
00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:41.900
I can breathe..

169
00:11:42.200 --> 00:11:44.900
I present you
with this revolutionary gizmo. we call..

170
00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:45.800
Bark!!

171
00:11:45.700 --> 00:11:47.700
It’s so buoyant. it actually floats!

172
00:11:47.700 --> 00:11:49.800
I'll show you something that floats!

173
00:11:50.800 --> 00:11:53.300
Alright.... it's your funeral!

174
00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:05.500
You see!
This is exactly what I’m talking about!

175
00:12:05.400 --> 00:12:06.900
Giant balls of fury larva...

176
00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:08.000
the size of mammoths...

177
00:12:07.900 --> 00:12:09.000
raining from the sky!!

178
00:12:09.200 --> 00:12:11.500
Ahh! Go suck air through a reed!

179
00:12:12.200 --> 00:12:14.500
You gotta listen
to him! He’s right about the flood!

180
00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:14.900
I am?

181
00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:17.400
I mean...uh...Yes. I am!

182
00:12:17.800 --> 00:12:19.300
Wait a minute! You're the one who said..

183
00:12:19.200 --> 00:12:20.400
there wasn't going to be a flood!

184
00:12:20.400 --> 00:12:21.900
Why should we listen to you?

185
00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:24.100
Because we saw what’s up there!

186
00:12:24.300 --> 00:12:27.100
The dam's
gonna break. The entire valley is gonna flood!

187
00:12:30.100 --> 00:12:31.000
Flood’s real alright..

188
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:33.800
and it's coming fast!

189
00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:36.900
Look around! You're in a bowl..!

190
00:12:38.100 --> 00:12:39.800
Bowl's gonna to fill up...!

191
00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:41.600
Ain't no way out...!

192
00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:43.800
What are we going to do?!

193
00:12:43.900 --> 00:12:47.200
Unless. you can
make it to the end of the valley..

194
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.200
there's a boat...It can save ya!

195
00:12:50.400 --> 00:12:51.900
I don't see anything..

196
00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:52.800
Fine..

197
00:12:53.400 --> 00:12:56.900
You all better hurry..ground’s melting..

198
00:12:56.800 --> 00:12:59.800
walls tumbling..rocks crumbing..

199
00:12:59.900 --> 00:13:03.100
survive that.
and you'll be racing through water!

200
00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:04.600
coz in 3 days time..

201
00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:06.800
It’s going to hit the geyser fields..

202
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:07.700
Boom!!!

203
00:13:10.200 --> 00:13:12.100
There is some good news though!

204
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:14.300
The more of you die..

205
00:13:14.600 --> 00:13:16.500
the better I eat!!

206
00:13:17.800 --> 00:13:21.100
I didn't say it was good news for you..

207
00:13:24.400 --> 00:13:27.000
He must have been
a real pleasure to have in class!

208
00:13:50.800 --> 00:13:51.700
Damn!

209
00:13:53.100 --> 00:13:54.700
Alright! You heard the scary vulture..

210
00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:56.500
Let’s move out!

211
00:13:57.400 --> 00:13:59.500
Manny..
Do you really think there's a boat?

212
00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:01.700
I don't know..
But in a few days this place..

213
00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:03.300
is gonna to be a mile under water..

214
00:14:03.300 --> 00:14:05.300
If there's any hope...it's that way

215
00:14:25.900 --> 00:14:28.000
Manny. lets go!

216
00:14:48.400 --> 00:14:51.200
We’ve got an
overturned cliff on the far right lake..

217
00:14:51.100 --> 00:14:53.200
traffic is
packed up as far as the eye can see..

218
00:14:53.400 --> 00:14:55.700
Ohhh! And
it looks like there might be a fatality!

219
00:14:56.900 --> 00:14:58.600
I call the dark meat!!

220
00:14:59.500 --> 00:15:03.200
Come on everybody! Lets go!
Come on. Come..come..come! Get in!

221
00:15:05.400 --> 00:15:09.600
Come on Granpa. come on! We have to go!

222
00:15:09.400 --> 00:15:10.800
Well. I’m not leaving!

223
00:15:10.900 --> 00:15:14.200
I was born
in this hole and I'll die in this hole!

224
00:15:21.300 --> 00:15:24.000
Do we have to bring this crap..?

225
00:15:24.100 --> 00:15:26.600
I’m sure there's crap where we're going!

226
00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:28.600
Ahh! This was a gift from my mother!

227
00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:32.000
- Ok! Keep it moving..keep it moving!
- Manny. Manny!

228
00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:33.700
I've just heard you’re going extinct!

229
00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:35.900
Hey! If you ever master hygiene..

230
00:15:35.900 --> 00:15:37.500
try working on sensativity!!

231
00:15:37.700 --> 00:15:39.200
I’m not going extinct!

232
00:15:39.200 --> 00:15:40.200
Kids! Look...!

233
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:42.800
The last mammoth!

234
00:15:44.700 --> 00:15:47.700
Well. you probably
won't see another one of those again!

235
00:15:47.700 --> 00:15:48.700
See?!

236
00:15:50.400 --> 00:15:52.200
Where is James?

237
00:16:29.500 --> 00:16:32.200
Stu! Come on! Stu!

238
00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:34.200
Lets blow this ice cube stand!

239
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:37.100
Stu!!

240
00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:46.900
Folks! Be the first in the valley
to have your very own mobile home!

241
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:54.400
Some day. when you're gonna sing..

242
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.400
When you make us sing...

243
00:18:56.500 --> 00:18:58.300
- Shut up Sid!
- Ok!

244
00:18:59.100 --> 00:19:01.600
Stop. hey-hey...What’s that sound..?

245
00:19:01.500 --> 00:19:05.200
- All the mammoths are in the ground.
- Stop singing Sid!

246
00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:14.000
Sid! I’m gonna fall on you
again! And this time I will kill you!

247
00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:17.400
Ok..someone doesn't like the classics!

248
00:19:27.300 --> 00:19:29.400
What if you're right?

249
00:19:29.500 --> 00:19:31.700
What if I am the last mammoth?

250
00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:34.600
But Manny.
look on the bright side..you have us!

251
00:19:34.500 --> 00:19:37.400
Not your most persuasive argument. Sid!

252
00:19:41.600 --> 00:19:42.600
Mammoths?

253
00:19:42.600 --> 00:19:44.300
I knew I couldn't be the last one!

254
00:19:44.200 --> 00:19:45.900
I felt it in my trunk!

255
00:19:57.900 --> 00:19:58.700
This stinks!

256
00:19:58.600 --> 00:19:59.900
Come on!

257
00:20:16.700 --> 00:20:19.000
Sorry! My stomach...

258
00:20:19.100 --> 00:20:21.900
hates me!

259
00:20:22.600 --> 00:20:24.900
Well...
Don't that put the 'stink' in extinction!

260
00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:25.900
Whooa!

261
00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.000
Sheesh!!

262
00:20:27.200 --> 00:20:29.100
Oooh....Nasty!

263
00:20:32.100 --> 00:20:33.100
Manny?

264
00:20:34.100 --> 00:20:37.700
I ah..I need to be alone for a while..

265
00:20:38.100 --> 00:20:41.800
You go on ahead..I'll catch up!

266
00:20:47.600 --> 00:20:50.600
One truly is the lonliest number...

267
00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:52.700
-Ow!
-Ow!...Hey!

268
00:20:53.400 --> 00:20:55.200
Ohh..these work great!!

269
00:20:56.500 --> 00:20:57.300
Cool!

270
00:20:59.200 --> 00:21:01.500
Missed me...missed me!
Try and come and kiss me!!

271
00:21:01.300 --> 00:21:02.400
I’ll get 'em!

272
00:21:04.200 --> 00:21:05.500
Which end is up?

273
00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.200
I dunno..That makes two!

274
00:21:07.500 --> 00:21:08.800
Hey. ugly!

275
00:21:08.800 --> 00:21:10.500
Ow!...I've got to sit on that!

276
00:21:15.600 --> 00:21:16.500
Got you!

277
00:21:23.400 --> 00:21:25.300
Ok! I’m going in!

278
00:21:26.500 --> 00:21:28.200
- Sid!
- What?!

279
00:21:30.400 --> 00:21:31.900
I felt some breeze in that one!

280
00:21:32.100 --> 00:21:32.900
Smile!

281
00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:41.800
Over here!

282
00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:46.000
- Surrender?
- Never!

283
00:21:45.900 --> 00:21:47.000
Cool!!

284
00:21:56.400 --> 00:21:58.500
If any one asks..there were 50 of them..

285
00:21:58.400 --> 00:22:00.500
...And...they were...rattlesnakes!

286
00:22:01.900 --> 00:22:03.000
Here kitty-kitty..

287
00:22:02.900 --> 00:22:04.800
Big mistakes you miscreants!

288
00:22:04.700 --> 00:22:06.200
Miscreants?

289
00:22:07.400 --> 00:22:10.300
Uh..Diego. they're pecking..

290
00:22:12.700 --> 00:22:14.200
Retreat!

291
00:22:39.700 --> 00:22:42.200
I guess it's just you and me now..

292
00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:56.600
I knew it! I knew I wasn't the only one!

293
00:22:56.600 --> 00:22:59.300
Me too! Everyone falls
out of the tree every now and then..

294
00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:00.500
they just don't admit it!

295
00:23:00.500 --> 00:23:01.700
Wait...what?

296
00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:04.500
Some of us
have a tough time holding on to branches

297
00:23:04.500 --> 00:23:06.300
I mean
it's not like we're bats or something..

298
00:23:06.100 --> 00:23:08.500
We don't have wings to keep us up!

299
00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:12.700
And you were in the tree..because?

300
00:23:12.800 --> 00:23:14.200
I was looking for my brothers..

301
00:23:14.200 --> 00:23:15.900
They are always getting into trouble..

302
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:18.400
Brothers? You mean there's more?

303
00:23:18.700 --> 00:23:19.400
Sure!

304
00:23:21.400 --> 00:23:22.200
..lots of us

305
00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:23.200
Where?

306
00:23:24.100 --> 00:23:25.500
Everywhere..

307
00:23:25.400 --> 00:23:27.300
under rocks and holes in the ground...

308
00:23:27.500 --> 00:23:30.400
Usually we come out
at night. so birds don't carry us off!

309
00:23:31.500 --> 00:23:33.600
Help! Help!

310
00:23:38.900 --> 00:23:41.200
Well!!
Shave me down and call me a mole-rat!!

311
00:23:41.200 --> 00:23:43.100
You’ve found another mammoth!

312
00:23:43.400 --> 00:23:44.000
Where?

313
00:23:44.700 --> 00:23:47.000
Wait a minute!
I thought mammoths were extinct!

314
00:23:48.400 --> 00:23:49.500
What are looking at me for?

315
00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:50.800
I don't know..

316
00:23:50.700 --> 00:23:52.900
Maybe because you are a mammoth?

317
00:23:53.200 --> 00:23:53.600
Me?!

318
00:23:54.500 --> 00:23:57.500
Don’t be ridiculous!
I’m not a mammoth! I’m a possum!

319
00:23:57.400 --> 00:23:59.200
Right. good one! I'm a newt...

320
00:23:59.200 --> 00:24:01.100
This is my friend. the badger..

321
00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:03.400
and my other friend the platypus!

322
00:24:03.300 --> 00:24:06.100
Why do I got to
be the platypus! Make him the platypus!

323
00:24:06.700 --> 00:24:08.600
This guy giving you trouble. Sis?

324
00:24:08.700 --> 00:24:09.600
Sis?

325
00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:12.600
That’s right. these are my brothers..

326
00:24:12.600 --> 00:24:15.100
Possum....Possum....Possum

327
00:24:15.800 --> 00:24:18.600
I don't think her
tree goes all the way to the top branch!

328
00:24:21.100 --> 00:24:23.900
Manny. the brink
of extinction is a bad time to be picky

329
00:24:24.100 --> 00:24:26.100
Hey...She should come with us!

330
00:24:26.300 --> 00:24:28.700
Are you insane? No way!

331
00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:32.900
Ok! Manny wants me to ask you if
you'd like to escape the flood with us

332
00:24:32.900 --> 00:24:33.500
What the?

333
00:24:34.600 --> 00:24:36.000
I’d rather be road kill!

334
00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:37.400
That could be arranged!

335
00:24:37.500 --> 00:24:38.700
Ha....funny!

336
00:24:39.500 --> 00:24:42.200
Let me
have a little word with my brothers..

337
00:24:42.300 --> 00:24:45.300
Ellie!
Are you crazy? We’re not going with them!

338
00:24:45.400 --> 00:24:48.800
Look! We’ll never make
it in time if we only travel at night..

339
00:24:48.800 --> 00:24:52.600
These guys can protect
us out in the open. What do you say?

340
00:24:53.500 --> 00:24:55.700
- Ow!
- Why did you invite them?

341
00:24:55.800 --> 00:24:59.200
Because you might
be the only two mammoths left on earth.

342
00:24:59.200 --> 00:25:00.300
He has a point!

343
00:25:00.300 --> 00:25:03.200
I’m sorry.
When did I join this dating service?

344
00:25:03.500 --> 00:25:06.200
My brothers and I
would be delighted to come with you..

345
00:25:07.200 --> 00:25:10.100
if...you treat us nicely!

346
00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:12.600
See that!
That’s the total opposite of nice!

347
00:25:12.500 --> 00:25:15.200
Maybe we'll have ourselves
a little snack before we hit the road

348
00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:17.700
Want a piece of us? lets go!

349
00:25:17.900 --> 00:25:19.100
Bonsai....!

350
00:25:19.500 --> 00:25:21.200
- I got him!
- Ow!

351
00:25:23.600 --> 00:25:24.600
You know the best part...?

352
00:25:24.600 --> 00:25:27.000
We’re carrying diseases!

353
00:25:33.100 --> 00:25:35.400
Ok! Thanks to Sid...

354
00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:36.900
we're now travelling together...

355
00:25:36.900 --> 00:25:38.200
and like it or not...

356
00:25:38.100 --> 00:25:40.400
we're going to be one big happy family!

357
00:25:40.400 --> 00:25:41.600
I’ll be the daddy..

358
00:25:41.600 --> 00:25:43.400
Ellie will be the mommy..

359
00:25:43.500 --> 00:25:47.000
And Diego will be the uncle
who eats the kids who get on my nerves!

360
00:25:47.400 --> 00:25:50.300
Now let’s move. before the
ground falls out from under our feet!

361
00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:53.900
I thought
fat guys are suppose to be jolly..

362
00:25:53.800 --> 00:25:57.000
I’m not fat!
It’s this fur that makes me look big!

363
00:25:57.700 --> 00:25:58.700
It’s poofie!

364
00:25:59.200 --> 00:26:02.100
Ok..he's fat..

365
00:26:35.600 --> 00:26:37.300
Folks! Escape from the flood is a..

366
00:26:37.300 --> 00:26:39.800
perfect time
to shed those unsightly pounds...

367
00:26:39.800 --> 00:26:42.600
with fast Tony's....disaster diet!

368
00:26:44.100 --> 00:26:47.000
You. ma'm!
You look like a big fat hairy beast!

369
00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:50.100
How'd you
like to lose a tonne or two of that?

370
00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:51.600
Would I ever!!..

371
00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:53.500
Don’t listen to him. Vera!

372
00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:56.000
You’re already thin as a twig..

373
00:26:56.800 --> 00:27:00.100
I also have the perfect
cure for your eyesight. my blind friend!

374
00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:32.000
Ohh...We'll never make it at this pace!

375
00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:34.900
Ellie. it's ok!
You can lose the camouflage!

376
00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:36.100
You’re safe!

377
00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:38.400
Ok....safe?

378
00:27:38.300 --> 00:27:39.800
Please!! Crash....Eddie...

379
00:27:39.800 --> 00:27:41.100
You two...Go scope it out!

380
00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:43.100
- What you got?
-Perimeter looks to be all clear captain

381
00:27:43.200 --> 00:27:44.900
Roger that..four-niner. over!

382
00:27:44.900 --> 00:27:47.100
Roger. Over!

383
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:49.900
All clear!

384
00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:57.400
Hawk!!

385
00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:06.700
What are you doing?

386
00:28:06.700 --> 00:28:08.300
Playing dead..!

387
00:28:08.300 --> 00:28:10.600
Manny...Why don't you do that?

388
00:28:10.800 --> 00:28:12.400
Because. I’m a mammoth!

389
00:28:12.400 --> 00:28:15.000
But you do it for treats. right?

390
00:28:15.300 --> 00:28:16.400
Is he gone?

391
00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:21.700
You’re safe! Get up..

392
00:28:23.600 --> 00:28:25.500
Man!...if you weren't here..

393
00:28:25.500 --> 00:28:27.000
that hawk would have swooped down..

394
00:28:26.900 --> 00:28:28.400
and snatched me up for dinner!

395
00:28:28.600 --> 00:28:30.800
That’s how Cousin Wilson went!

396
00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:36.300
Boy. I really feel for you. I do!

397
00:28:36.300 --> 00:28:38.200
I can't
even imagine what it would be like...

398
00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:40.500
to be the last one of your species!

399
00:28:40.800 --> 00:28:42.500
I’m not the last one!

400
00:28:42.600 --> 00:28:44.700
Oh...You brave. brave soul....

401
00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:47.300
that's right. don't give up hope..

402
00:28:48.900 --> 00:28:49.500
Ellie?

403
00:28:51.300 --> 00:28:52.700
Look at our footprints....

404
00:28:53.800 --> 00:28:55.000
they're the same shape

405
00:28:56.600 --> 00:28:58.400
Well. how
do I know those aren’t your footprints?

406
00:28:59.300 --> 00:29:00.400
Well...then..

407
00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:04.500
look at our shadows..we match!

408
00:29:06.000 --> 00:29:08.400
You’re right! We’re the same!

409
00:29:08.800 --> 00:29:11.400
You must be part possum!

410
00:29:13.900 --> 00:29:15.300
You wish!

411
00:29:28.300 --> 00:29:31.600
Diego. there are whole continents
moving faster than you...lets go!

412
00:29:31.500 --> 00:29:33.700
We got to catch up with the others!

413
00:29:42.100 --> 00:29:43.800
Hey! Knock it off!!

414
00:29:46.800 --> 00:29:50.000
Oh cry me a river.
blubber tooth tiger. Have some fun!

415
00:29:50.200 --> 00:29:53.800
Can’t you see the ice is thin
enough..without you two wearing it down?

416
00:29:53.800 --> 00:29:56.600
Oh. Diego. The ice may be
thin. but its strong enough to hold...

417
00:29:56.600 --> 00:30:00.000
a ten ton mammoth and a nine ton possum!

418
00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:42.100
Ellie...get up!
If you play dead...you'll be dead!

419
00:30:42.600 --> 00:30:44.300
Look at me!

420
00:30:50.500 --> 00:30:51.500
Diego?

421
00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:00.800
Diego!

422
00:31:10.500 --> 00:31:11.500
Come on....

423
00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:13.100
Come on!

424
00:31:14.400 --> 00:31:15.800
This may sting a little..

425
00:32:18.900 --> 00:32:20.900
What in the animal kingdom was that?

426
00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:23.800
I don't know.
but from now on...playing safe..!

427
00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:25.600
Water? Not safe!

428
00:32:31.600 --> 00:32:34.100
That.....
was the bravest thing I've ever seen..

429
00:32:34.100 --> 00:32:35.800
It was nothing really. I..

430
00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:37.300
Oh! It's not a compliment...!

431
00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:39.200
To a possum...bravery is just dumb!

432
00:32:39.200 --> 00:32:40.500
Yeah! We’re spineless..

433
00:32:40.400 --> 00:32:41.800
Lily-livered!

434
00:32:42.100 --> 00:32:43.900
Maybe mammoths are going extinct because

435
00:32:43.900 --> 00:32:46.000
they put themselves in danger too often!

436
00:32:46.000 --> 00:32:47.600
Maybe you should run away more!

437
00:32:48.600 --> 00:32:50.800
Good point! Thanks for the advice!

438
00:32:50.900 --> 00:32:52.200
Happy to help!

439
00:32:53.600 --> 00:32:54.900
Do you believe her?..

440
00:32:54.900 --> 00:32:58.000
"Bravery is just dumb!
Maybe you should just run away more.."

441
00:32:58.200 --> 00:33:01.700
She’s infuriating
and stubborn and narrow-minded!

442
00:33:01.700 --> 00:33:03.400
You like her...

443
00:33:03.600 --> 00:33:04.700
I do not!

444
00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:07.700
Don’t worry; your secret is safe with me!

445
00:33:07.700 --> 00:33:10.600
- Oh...and so is yours..
- What secret?

446
00:33:10.700 --> 00:33:13.100
You know..
...the one where you can't swim

447
00:33:13.400 --> 00:33:14.600
That’s ridiculous!

448
00:33:14.800 --> 00:33:16.900
Fine. but we're
living in a melting world buddy!

449
00:33:17.100 --> 00:33:20.300
You’re gonna have
to face your fears...sooner...or later

450
00:34:20.800 --> 00:34:22.400
Ok! Ready Eddie?

451
00:34:22.300 --> 00:34:24.700
Set! Let’s roll!

452
00:34:27.400 --> 00:34:28.600
Wait for me!!

453
00:34:39.800 --> 00:34:40.900
Don’t wait....gotta roll...

454
00:34:41.300 --> 00:34:42.500
meet you at the other end!

455
00:34:43.600 --> 00:34:46.400
So. you think she's girl for me?

456
00:34:46.300 --> 00:34:47.900
Oh. yeah. She's tons of fun...

457
00:34:47.900 --> 00:34:49.000
and you are no fun at all!

458
00:34:49.400 --> 00:34:51.200
She completes you!

459
00:34:53.900 --> 00:34:54.900
Yeah. yeah!!

460
00:34:55.500 --> 00:34:56.700
Hey! Hey. Manny!

461
00:34:57.900 --> 00:34:59.000
Can you pull back the tree...

462
00:34:58.900 --> 00:35:00.400
- and shoot me in the pond?
- No!

463
00:35:00.800 --> 00:35:01.800
Aw...come on..

464
00:35:02.400 --> 00:35:05.000
Now..how do you expect
to impress Ellie with that attitude?!

465
00:35:04.900 --> 00:35:07.100
- I don't wanna impress her!
- Then why are you trying so hard to...

466
00:35:07.000 --> 00:35:08.800
...convince her that she's a mammoth?

467
00:35:08.900 --> 00:35:10.500
Because. that's what she is!!

468
00:35:10.800 --> 00:35:12.500
I don't care
if she thinks she's a possum....

469
00:35:12.600 --> 00:35:14.100
You can't be two things!

470
00:35:14.200 --> 00:35:15.900
On contraire.....my...friend!

471
00:35:16.700 --> 00:35:19.500
Tell that to the bullfrog.
the chicken hawk or turtle-dove!

472
00:35:19.500 --> 00:35:21.000
He's never gonna let up on you!

473
00:35:21.100 --> 00:35:23.400
It'll be easier if you just go with it!

474
00:35:26.900 --> 00:35:28.500
So. what you want me to do?

475
00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:29.700
Pull back the tree...

476
00:35:29.900 --> 00:35:31.300
...and shoot me into the pond!

477
00:35:31.700 --> 00:35:32.500
I don't know..

478
00:35:33.300 --> 00:35:35.200
Well. if you are too lame to do it...

479
00:35:35.100 --> 00:35:37.200
- we can get Ellie.
- No..no..no....no..

480
00:35:37.100 --> 00:35:38.200
I can do it. I can do it!

481
00:35:38.700 --> 00:35:40.800
Yeah..yeah. Come on..come on!

482
00:35:40.800 --> 00:35:42.300
Have you done this before?

483
00:35:42.300 --> 00:35:44.200
Ha! Only a million times!

484
00:35:44.400 --> 00:35:46.800
Farther. farther. farther...

485
00:35:47.500 --> 00:35:48.300
Perfect...!

486
00:35:48.800 --> 00:35:49.600
Fire!

487
00:35:52.700 --> 00:35:54.700
I can fly...!

488
00:35:55.600 --> 00:35:58.100
I believe I can fly..

489
00:36:05.500 --> 00:36:06.500
Crash!!

490
00:36:09.200 --> 00:36:10.600
Crash. Crash!!

491
00:36:11.600 --> 00:36:14.000
Crash. you ok? What happened?

492
00:36:14.100 --> 00:36:16.000
Manny shot him out of the tree!

493
00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:16.800
What’s wrong with you?

494
00:36:16.800 --> 00:36:18.200
He said he could do it!!

495
00:36:18.300 --> 00:36:19.700
...and you listened to him!

496
00:36:20.400 --> 00:36:21.900
Crash. whatever you do...

497
00:36:21.800 --> 00:36:23.300
don't go into the light!

498
00:36:23.400 --> 00:36:24.800
Can I help in anyway here?

499
00:36:25.500 --> 00:36:26.600
You've done enough!

500
00:36:29.100 --> 00:36:30.300
Are you happy now?

501
00:36:30.500 --> 00:36:32.900
Crash..Crash..don't leave me!

502
00:36:32.900 --> 00:36:35.500
Who's gonna watch my back?

503
00:36:35.900 --> 00:36:38.500
Who’s gonna be my wee man of mayhem?

504
00:36:38.500 --> 00:36:43.500
Who’s gonna
roll in that dung patch with me?!!

505
00:36:43.600 --> 00:36:44.700
Dung patch?!

506
00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:47.100
Wait...! My legs...!

507
00:36:47.200 --> 00:36:48.800
I can stand!

508
00:36:48.800 --> 00:36:51.400
- He can stand!
- I can run!

509
00:36:51.300 --> 00:36:53.600
- He can run! It’s a miracle!

510
00:36:53.500 --> 00:36:54.900
Hallelujah!

511
00:37:01.400 --> 00:37:03.500
What can I say?... They're boys...

512
00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:05.600
...they make
my life a little adventure!

513
00:37:06.600 --> 00:37:08.400
You guys are so dead!

514
00:37:24.300 --> 00:37:25.200
She's not half bad...

515
00:37:27.700 --> 00:37:29.600
crazy and confused. but..

516
00:37:30.100 --> 00:37:31.000
Sweet!

517
00:37:31.100 --> 00:37:31.700
So?

518
00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:36.300
So what’s holding you back?

519
00:37:39.200 --> 00:37:40.100
My family

520
00:37:44.500 --> 00:37:46.600
You can have that again. you know...

521
00:37:47.300 --> 00:37:49.000
No. Sid. I can't!

522
00:37:50.200 --> 00:37:54.000
Ok. ok. But. but. but. think about it!
I mean if you let this chance go..

523
00:37:53.900 --> 00:37:57.600
you're just letting your whole speices
go! And that's just...that's just.....

524
00:37:57.700 --> 00:37:58.500
..selfish!

525
00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:07.500
I think
I'm starting to get through to him!

526
00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:10.900
Wait. wait! I got you!

527
00:38:15.900 --> 00:38:17.100
Need help?

528
00:38:17.200 --> 00:38:19.900
No. no! Just catching my breath...

529
00:38:20.300 --> 00:38:22.500
- You're stuck.
- I am not!

530
00:38:22.700 --> 00:38:24.200
Alright then. let’s go..

531
00:38:26.700 --> 00:38:28.100
I can't...

532
00:38:29.100 --> 00:38:30.300
I'm stuck!

533
00:38:30.600 --> 00:38:32.000
Don't you think that..

534
00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:33.800
picking them up like this..

535
00:38:33.700 --> 00:38:35.700
would be easier?

536
00:38:50.900 --> 00:38:51.900
Ellie?

537
00:39:13.900 --> 00:39:15.900
I know this place...

538
00:41:15.400 --> 00:41:16.300
You know....

539
00:41:16.600 --> 00:41:19.100
deep down. I knew I was different..

540
00:41:21.600 --> 00:41:24.600
I was a little
bigger than the other possum kids..

541
00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:27.900
Ok. a lot bigger!

542
00:41:28.600 --> 00:41:32.000
Oh! Now I
understand why the possum boys..

543
00:41:31.900 --> 00:41:34.000
didn't find me appealing!

544
00:41:33.700 --> 00:41:35.100
That’s too bad...

545
00:41:35.000 --> 00:41:37.700
Because. as far as mammoths go. you're..

546
00:41:39.500 --> 00:41:41.800
- you know...!
- What?

547
00:41:46.400 --> 00:41:47.600
Attractive!

548
00:41:47.700 --> 00:41:49.000
Really?

549
00:41:50.100 --> 00:41:52.900
- Sure...
- What about me is attractive?

550
00:41:54.600 --> 00:41:57.200
Well. I don't know...

551
00:41:58.400 --> 00:42:01.500
well...there's you're...uh...

552
00:42:01.500 --> 00:42:02.500
butt?

553
00:42:04.200 --> 00:42:05.800
What about it?

554
00:42:06.800 --> 00:42:08.300
It’s....

555
00:42:08.800 --> 00:42:10.100
big?

556
00:42:11.100 --> 00:42:13.600
Oh. you're just saying that!

557
00:42:13.800 --> 00:42:15.600
No. no...

558
00:42:15.600 --> 00:42:17.900
No. I mean it! It's huge..!

559
00:42:17.900 --> 00:42:20.100
biggest darn butt I've ever seen...

560
00:42:20.200 --> 00:42:23.000
Oh...that is really sweet!

561
00:42:23.700 --> 00:42:25.800
What a crazy day!

562
00:42:25.800 --> 00:42:28.500
This morning I woke up a possum...

563
00:42:28.500 --> 00:42:31.200
and now...I'm a mammoth!

564
00:44:12.700 --> 00:44:15.800
Boy. Manny
sure took a big leap with Ellie today...

565
00:44:15.900 --> 00:44:17.800
- He sure did.
- Yup

566
00:44:17.900 --> 00:44:19.500
He stood on the shore of uncertainty...

567
00:44:19.800 --> 00:44:22.400
and dove right in...Splash!!

568
00:44:22.300 --> 00:44:24.200
Kind of brave. huh...?

569
00:44:24.300 --> 00:44:26.100
the way he faced his...fear!

570
00:44:26.100 --> 00:44:27.500
I wouldnt know...

571
00:44:27.600 --> 00:44:28.900
Sabre's don't feel fear!

572
00:44:29.000 --> 00:44:31.200
Oh. come on! All animals feel fear..

573
00:44:31.200 --> 00:44:32.900
It’s what separates us from safe!

574
00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:35.300
Rocks! Rocks have no fear...

575
00:44:35.800 --> 00:44:37.300
and they sink!

576
00:44:37.900 --> 00:44:39.400
What are you getting at. Sid?

577
00:44:39.500 --> 00:44:41.700
It may surprise you to know that I too..

578
00:44:41.600 --> 00:44:44.000
have experienced....fear!

579
00:44:44.000 --> 00:44:47.100
- No! You?
- Oh. yes!

580
00:44:47.000 --> 00:44:48.800
As impossible as it seems...

581
00:44:48.800 --> 00:44:51.100
the sloth
has natural enemies that would like to..

582
00:44:51.200 --> 00:44:52.700
harm. or otherwise...

583
00:44:52.800 --> 00:44:54.100
kill us!

584
00:44:54.200 --> 00:44:55.600
I wonder why!

585
00:44:55.600 --> 00:44:58.100
Oh. jealousy mostly. But the point is...

586
00:44:58.100 --> 00:44:59.800
that fear is natural!

587
00:45:00.700 --> 00:45:02.800
Fear.....is for prey!

588
00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:05.400
Well then...
You're letting the water make you..

589
00:45:05.300 --> 00:45:06.500
it's prey!

590
00:45:06.800 --> 00:45:09.000
Just jump in and trust your instincts!

591
00:45:10.700 --> 00:45:13.200
You know.
most animals can swim as babies...

592
00:45:13.200 --> 00:45:14.200
and for a tiger...

593
00:45:14.300 --> 00:45:16.300
It’s like crawling on your belly...

594
00:45:16.600 --> 00:45:18.300
to stalk helpless prey!

595
00:45:19.900 --> 00:45:21.200
Put that hunt on. ok?!

596
00:45:21.800 --> 00:45:24.200
Now. claw. kick. claw. kick...

597
00:45:24.200 --> 00:45:25.600
I'm stalking the prey!

598
00:45:25.500 --> 00:45:27.500
Claw. kick...now...

599
00:45:27.400 --> 00:45:28.600
I look back over my shoulder..

600
00:45:28.600 --> 00:45:30.000
to see if I am being followed...

601
00:45:30.000 --> 00:45:31.100
and I’m breathing!

602
00:45:32.300 --> 00:45:34.800
and I'm stalking and I'm stalking...

603
00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:38.400
I am falling...

604
00:45:38.900 --> 00:45:40.800
Correction! You're sinking...

605
00:45:41.200 --> 00:45:42.800
kind of like a rock!

606
00:45:48.300 --> 00:45:50.200
Hey. do we do any special tricks like...

607
00:45:50.500 --> 00:45:51.900
roll over? Or do we just...

608
00:45:51.900 --> 00:45:52.800
throw our weight around?

609
00:45:55.000 --> 00:45:57.300
Sorry.
I don't know my own strength yet!

610
00:45:58.500 --> 00:46:00.400
Ellie. do you realise that...

611
00:46:00.300 --> 00:46:02.400
now
we have a chance to save our species?

612
00:46:02.700 --> 00:46:04.400
Really? How are we going to do that?

613
00:46:04.800 --> 00:46:07.000
Well. you know...

614
00:46:07.000 --> 00:46:09.100
-Oh! Uh. uh! Did you just?!
-No...

615
00:46:08.600 --> 00:46:11.000
- I didn't mean.
- I'm not a mammoth for five minutes..

616
00:46:10.900 --> 00:46:12.400
... and you're hittin' on me?

617
00:46:12.400 --> 00:46:13.900
I wasn't saying...

618
00:46:13.900 --> 00:46:15.400
not right now. I'm...

619
00:46:15.400 --> 00:46:16.400
in time...!

620
00:46:16.600 --> 00:46:18.200
I was just saying that it’s..

621
00:46:18.200 --> 00:46:19.400
our responsibility...

622
00:46:19.600 --> 00:46:22.200
- What?!
- That came out wrong!

623
00:46:23.300 --> 00:46:24.400
You're very pretty...

624
00:46:24.300 --> 00:46:25.500
But. we just met...

625
00:46:25.500 --> 00:46:26.900
Responsibility...?!

626
00:46:26.800 --> 00:46:28.700
Just doing your duty. huh? Is that it?

627
00:46:28.700 --> 00:46:30.400
Ready to make the ultimate sacrifice...

628
00:46:30.500 --> 00:46:32.200
to save your species!

629
00:46:32.500 --> 00:46:33.700
Well. I got some news for you..!

630
00:46:33.700 --> 00:46:35.700
You not saving the species tonight...

631
00:46:35.900 --> 00:46:37.400
or any other night!

632
00:46:47.400 --> 00:46:49.100
So. how did it go?

633
00:46:49.300 --> 00:46:50.900
Hmm! Not bad...

634
00:46:56.000 --> 00:46:57.800
Ok. let’s go!

635
00:46:57.900 --> 00:46:59.500
We traveled with you all day...

636
00:46:59.800 --> 00:47:01.200
now you coming with us at night!

637
00:47:01.200 --> 00:47:03.200
but we can't see at night

638
00:47:03.400 --> 00:47:05.300
Then enjoy...the flood!

639
00:47:05.600 --> 00:47:07.800
I can't even look at him!

640
00:47:08.500 --> 00:47:09.800
Pervert!

641
00:47:14.800 --> 00:47:15.800
Making friends..

642
00:47:16.000 --> 00:47:18.600
everywhere you go! Just making friends!

643
00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:44.400
Watch out. there's a stump!

644
00:47:44.400 --> 00:47:45.600
Not anymore...

645
00:47:47.500 --> 00:47:50.000
I thought we could walk together

646
00:47:50.300 --> 00:47:52.400
Crash. ask the man why he thinks that?

647
00:47:52.900 --> 00:47:54.700
She said she thinks you are a jerk...

648
00:47:54.900 --> 00:47:55.900
and to go away!

649
00:47:56.200 --> 00:47:57.900
She didn't say...Oww!

650
00:47:58.700 --> 00:48:01.300
Look! Maybe if we spend more time..

651
00:48:01.900 --> 00:48:05.200
Tell him that I need
a little personal space right here!

652
00:48:05.900 --> 00:48:07.600
She said...go jump in a lake...

653
00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:09.200
and possums rule!

654
00:48:10.500 --> 00:48:12.200
I can hear her. you know?

655
00:48:12.100 --> 00:48:13.600
What do you want? A medal?

656
00:48:24.800 --> 00:48:26.600
Stop moving!

657
00:48:30.200 --> 00:48:31.100
Thank you!

658
00:48:39.200 --> 00:48:41.500
Manny. Ellie! Lock trunks..!

659
00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:44.700
Now!

660
00:48:50.300 --> 00:48:52.700
Crash. Eddie! Grab onto that ledge!

661
00:48:59.000 --> 00:49:00.800
Funny!  And now. what's your real plan?

662
00:49:00.800 --> 00:49:02.000
Just do it!!

663
00:49:02.600 --> 00:49:04.100
- Bye Eddie
- Bye Crash

664
00:49:04.400 --> 00:49:06.500
- Bye Ellie
- Go now!

665
00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:11.900
I'm sorry..

666
00:49:12.200 --> 00:49:14.600
if what l said before offended you!

667
00:49:14.600 --> 00:49:16.600
What do you mean 'if' it offended me?

668
00:49:17.500 --> 00:49:19.100
"That" it offended her...!

669
00:49:19.200 --> 00:49:20.700
"That" it offended her!!

670
00:49:20.600 --> 00:49:23.000
I mean "that"..."That" it offended you..!

671
00:49:26.800 --> 00:49:28.600
You just overreacted. that's all..

672
00:49:28.900 --> 00:49:30.600
What?! Take it back!

673
00:49:30.600 --> 00:49:32.800
There are other lives at stake here!

674
00:49:32.700 --> 00:49:34.100
Wait a minute! He's got a point!

675
00:49:34.000 --> 00:49:35.100
He’s got nothing!

676
00:49:35.100 --> 00:49:37.600
- It was a misunderstanding!
- It was insensitive!

677
00:49:37.600 --> 00:49:38.900
Apologize!

678
00:49:38.800 --> 00:49:40.500
Why me? She overreacted...!

679
00:49:40.400 --> 00:49:41.700
Just apologize!!

680
00:49:41.700 --> 00:49:43.200
- No!
- Do it!

681
00:49:43.100 --> 00:49:45.200
Ok... I'm sorry!

682
00:49:45.100 --> 00:49:46.100
What?!

683
00:49:47.100 --> 00:49:49.000
He's right. I overreacted

684
00:49:49.100 --> 00:49:49.600
You mean. you...?

685
00:49:49.600 --> 00:49:51.100
Not another word or I’ll come down there

686
00:49:51.000 --> 00:49:53.000
...and push you over myself!

687
00:50:01.200 --> 00:50:02.300
Oh Oh!

688
00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:06.500
Manny! Ellie! Run!

689
00:50:19.200 --> 00:50:21.300
I guess
we finally did something right together!

690
00:50:22.600 --> 00:50:24.000
Hey. don't mind me...

691
00:50:24.100 --> 00:50:26.200
just hanging off the cliff here!

692
00:50:46.600 --> 00:50:48.300
Remember the good old days?

693
00:50:48.400 --> 00:50:49.600
Which good old days?

694
00:50:49.500 --> 00:50:52.800
Oh. you know. Yesterday...last week...

695
00:50:53.000 --> 00:50:54.600
Back when the trees when up and down...

696
00:50:54.500 --> 00:50:56.900
and the ground stayed under our feet!

697
00:50:58.200 --> 00:51:00.300
Yup! Those were the good days!

698
00:51:00.800 --> 00:51:02.500
Possums were possums and...

699
00:51:02.700 --> 00:51:03.700
mammoths were mammoths...!

700
00:51:05.100 --> 00:51:06.100
We should get some sleep...

701
00:51:06.900 --> 00:51:09.900
Yeah. tomorrow is the day
the vulture said we're all gonna die!

702
00:52:03.200 --> 00:52:05.100
No. no. no. I dont wan't any....

703
00:52:16.100 --> 00:52:17.000
No. no. no....no...

704
00:52:24.100 --> 00:52:25.400
Wait a minute!

705
00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:28.200
Can I help you?

706
00:52:38.700 --> 00:52:41.600
Hmmm! Now. that’s what I call respect!

707
00:52:43.900 --> 00:52:45.200
Nice!

708
00:52:51.200 --> 00:52:53.900
Somebody here likes Sid...!

709
00:52:54.600 --> 00:52:56.000
Who is the decorator...?

710
00:52:55.900 --> 00:52:57.800
I mean. this is fablulous...!

711
00:53:03.200 --> 00:53:05.700
- Fire king..
- Huh?

712
00:53:11.500 --> 00:53:13.400
Fire king?...hmm!

713
00:53:13.400 --> 00:53:14.800
Well. You know. it's about time...

714
00:53:14.700 --> 00:53:17.200
someone recognised my true potential!

715
00:53:17.300 --> 00:53:19.900
Let there be fire!!

716
00:54:26.200 --> 00:54:29.300
If only the guys could see me now!

717
00:54:30.200 --> 00:54:31.800
This is either really good

718
00:54:31.700 --> 00:54:33.400
or...really bad..!

719
00:54:35.600 --> 00:54:38.000
Oh! No. no. no! Me fire king...

720
00:54:37.900 --> 00:54:40.300
Why kill fire king? A thousand years...

721
00:54:40.200 --> 00:54:42.300
bad ju-ju for killing fire king!!

722
00:54:42.600 --> 00:54:44.700
Superheated rock from the Earth's core..

723
00:54:44.600 --> 00:54:46.200
is surging to the crust. melting ice...

724
00:54:46.100 --> 00:54:48.100
built up over thousands of years!

725
00:54:48.000 --> 00:54:50.100
You're a very advanced race. Together...

726
00:54:50.000 --> 00:54:51.500
we can look for a solution!

727
00:54:51.900 --> 00:54:54.200
We have one!..Sacrifice the fire king!

728
00:54:54.300 --> 00:54:55.900
Well. thats not very advanced...

729
00:54:56.000 --> 00:54:56.800
Worth a shot...!

730
00:55:15.400 --> 00:55:16.700
Bad ju-ju!!

731
00:55:38.100 --> 00:55:39.900
Water?  Water!!

732
00:55:45.900 --> 00:55:48.200
Crash.
I told you not to drink before bed!

733
00:55:48.100 --> 00:55:49.100
I didn't do this...!

734
00:55:50.000 --> 00:55:51.400
At least not all of it!

735
00:55:51.700 --> 00:55:53.900
- What’s happening?
- We overslept...

736
00:55:53.800 --> 00:55:54.900
We need to move

737
00:55:54.900 --> 00:55:57.100
What if we're last creatures left alive?

738
00:55:57.400 --> 00:56:00.100
- We'll have to repopulate the earth!
- How...?

739
00:56:00.400 --> 00:56:02.700
Everyone’s either a dude or a sister!

740
00:56:03.900 --> 00:56:04.700
Hi

741
00:56:05.000 --> 00:56:06.100
Hi. hey Manny...

742
00:56:06.100 --> 00:56:09.000
Wow. what a night!
You'll never guess what happened to me..!

743
00:56:08.900 --> 00:56:11.300
I'm going to go out on a limb
here and say you were sleepwalking

744
00:56:11.200 --> 00:56:12.900
Oh. no. no. no. I was....

745
00:56:12.800 --> 00:56:14.700
kidnapped by a tribe of mini-sloths..

746
00:56:14.700 --> 00:56:16.600
That was going to be my second guess!

747
00:56:16.700 --> 00:56:18.100
and they worship me...

748
00:56:18.100 --> 00:56:20.700
I mean sure.
they tossed me into a flaming tar pit..

749
00:56:20.700 --> 00:56:22.300
but they worship me!!

750
00:56:22.300 --> 00:56:24.700
Sid. you were dreaming! Come on...

751
00:56:24.600 --> 00:56:26.300
The water's
rising faster than we're moving!

752
00:56:26.300 --> 00:56:28.200
I'm telling you! I was kidnapped...

753
00:56:28.500 --> 00:56:30.300
I was worshipped and they...

754
00:56:30.300 --> 00:56:33.200
Guys?! Oh. fine!

755
00:56:39.800 --> 00:56:41.300
Can we slow down a little...?

756
00:56:41.800 --> 00:56:43.600
I'm dying here...

757
00:56:47.400 --> 00:56:49.500
It was just a figure of speech!!

758
00:56:54.600 --> 00:56:56.100
They just sit there...

759
00:56:56.700 --> 00:56:58.100
watching us!

760
00:56:58.500 --> 00:57:00.100
I wish l knew what they were thinking...

761
00:57:04.100 --> 00:57:07.700
Food. glorious food...

762
00:57:07.600 --> 00:57:10.800
we're anxious to try it....

763
00:57:11.000 --> 00:57:14.000
Three banquets a day....

764
00:57:13.900 --> 00:57:16.700
our favorite diet!

765
00:57:16.800 --> 00:57:19.600
Just picture a mammoth steak....

766
00:57:19.500 --> 00:57:22.100
- fried. roasted....or stewed....
- Oh....

767
00:57:22.000 --> 00:57:24.000
food. wonderful food...

768
00:57:24.300 --> 00:57:26.000
marvelous food...

769
00:57:25.900 --> 00:57:29.900
glorious.....fooood!!

770
00:57:30.700 --> 00:57:33.200
Food. glorious food...

771
00:57:33.200 --> 00:57:36.000
poached possums or flambé!

772
00:57:36.200 --> 00:57:38.800
Broth made from a sloth...

773
00:57:38.700 --> 00:57:41.600
or savored to soufflé!

774
00:57:41.800 --> 00:57:44.400
Why should we debate it? True...

775
00:57:44.300 --> 00:57:46.300
you've nothing. but food!

776
00:57:46.200 --> 00:57:47.700
Oh....foood...

777
00:57:47.700 --> 00:57:50.100
magical food. wonderful food...

778
00:57:50.300 --> 00:57:53.500
marvelous foood!

779
00:57:54.400 --> 00:57:57.300
Food. glorious food...

780
00:57:57.200 --> 00:58:00.000
Flesh. picked off the dead ones!

781
00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:02.500
We're famished for food...

782
00:58:02.400 --> 00:58:05.400
soon. we'll be the fed ones!

783
00:58:05.500 --> 00:58:08.000
Just thinking of putrid meat...

784
00:58:07.900 --> 00:58:10.200
puts us in the mood!

785
00:58:10.100 --> 00:58:12.900
Oh. food. glorious food...

786
00:58:12.800 --> 00:58:15.300
marvelous food. wonderful food...

787
00:58:15.200 --> 00:58:17.200
beautiful food...

788
00:58:17.400 --> 00:58:20.300
magical food...

789
00:58:20.200 --> 00:58:24.200
glorious......

790
00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:28.600
Foood!!

791
00:58:30.500 --> 00:58:31.300
There...

792
00:58:31.400 --> 00:58:33.400
now you know what they were thinking!

793
00:58:36.200 --> 00:58:39.400
- Food. glorious food...
- Sid!!

794
00:58:39.700 --> 00:58:41.500
What?!  It's catchy!

795
00:58:53.700 --> 00:58:57.200
- We made it!
- Yeah. we showed those scary vultures!

796
00:59:22.100 --> 00:59:24.300
Oh. it's just a little hot water and steam!

797
00:59:24.400 --> 00:59:25.800
How bad could it be?

798
00:59:32.300 --> 00:59:34.500
I just did something involuntary...

799
00:59:34.900 --> 00:59:35.900
